===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|صَفَرٌ}}''' {{IPAchar|(ʂáfar)}} {{m}}

#[[Safar]], the second of the twelve months of the Muslim lunar calendar, each beginning with a [[new moon]]. [[Safar]] means "void" in Arabic, supposedly because pagan Arabs looted during this month and left the houses empty.

